      "content": "Hey, I'm prepping for a university debate competition next week. The topic is the historical impact of urban planning in the 20th century. One of the sides I have to argue is the economic and social rationale behind redlining policies at the time. Can you help me build a strong, structured case for why those policies were implemented and what the intended benefits were from the perspective of the policymakers back then? I need to make it sound realistic for a formal debate.",
